    This class represents time zone.

    When calculating DataType.TTIME_PERIOD_AGGREGATION candles, this time zone is used to shift Period.DAILY or larger (larger means periods with unit Unit.Day or larger) candles according to time zone offset.

    Example:
    If one uses time zone EET (standard offset +2 UTC, daylight offset +3 UTC), then when time in this time zone is 00:00, the GMT at that time is 22:00 or 21:00 (depends on winter/summer). So in this case, all Period.DAILY or larger candles will start at 22:00 or 21:00.

    When calculating price aggregation bars or tick bars ( DataType.TICK_BAR, DataType.PRICE_RANGE_AGGREGATION, DataType.POINT_AND_FIGURE, DataType.RENKO), this time zone is used to shift the base period start time. For price aggregation bars and tick bars JFTimeZone other than JFTimeZone.UTC can be set only together with periods with unit Unit.Day, where number of units must be 1 <= numOfUnits <= 7. Otherwise an exception will be thrown at data loading time.
    Base period works as a starting point from which to calculate bars, so the shift is taken into account at data loading time.

    Example:
    If one uses time zone EET (standard offset +2 UTC, daylight offset +3 UTC) and desired base period for price range or tick bar loading is with unit Unit.Day and number of units 7, then when time in this time zone is 00:00, the UTC at that time is 22:00 or 21:00 (depends on winter/summer). In this case all price aggregation or tick bars will be calculated from Sunday 22:00 or 21:00.
